        <svcproc svcproctype="repair" graphiccount="2">
            <title>Service Procedure</title>
            <specpara>
                <warning>
                    <para>To avoid property damage, personal injury, or death, park the vehicle on a flat level surface,
                        set the parking brake, turn the engine off and chock the rear wheels.
                    </para>
                </warning>
            </specpara>
            <specpara>
                <warning>
                    <para>Always use floor stands to support the vehicle before working on it. Using only a jack could
                        allow the vehicle to fall resulting in property damage, personal injury, or death.
                    </para>
                </warning>
            </specpara>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Raise the front axle until the tires are no longer in contact with the floor.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the fill plug (Figure 1, Item 5), drain the oil, remove the hub cap and gasket
                    (Figure 1, Item 1).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f049071" figsize="pg-wide">
                <graphic filename="../afcfigures/g049071b.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="514px"
                         scalefitheight="328px"/>
                <caption>Figure 1. Front Steer Axle Spindle Assembly</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. Hub Cap</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. PRO-TORQ&#174; Nut Assembly</callout1>
                    <callout1>3. Spindle Washer</callout1>
                    <callout1>4. Hub Cap Mounting Screws (6)</callout1>
                    <callout1>5. Fill Plug</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Insert a small screwdriver (Figure 2, Item 3) and carefully remove the nut keeper
                    (Figure 2, Item 1) from the internal groove in the nut.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the nut.</para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f049072" figsize="pg-wide">
                <graphic filename="../afcfigures/g049072a.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="752px"
                         scalefitheight="328px"/>
                <caption>Figure 2. PRO-TORQ&#174; Spindle Nut Assembly</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. Keeper</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. PRO-TORQ Nut</callout1>
                    <callout1>3. Pry Here with Small Screwdriver</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install washer, Part Number 1663196C1, onto the spindle and against the wheel bearing.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">
                    <emph type="bold">A.</emph>Reinstall the PRO-TORQ nut and tighten to 180 to 220 Lbf-ft (244 to 298
                    Nm) while rotating the hub assembly a minimum of one complete revolution.
                </para>
                <para>
                    <emph type="bold">B.</emph>Back off the nut 1/2 turn and re-tighten to 45 to 55 Lbf-ft (61 to 75
                    Nm).
                </para>
                <para>
                    <emph type="bold">C.</emph>Back off the nut 1/8 turn to achieve a final end play setting of 0.001 to
                    0.005 inch. End play must be verified with a magnetic base dial indicator.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Reinstall the PRO-TORQ nut keeper making sure it is seated in the internal groove in the
                    nut. If the keeper cannot be fully seated in the groove, do not loosen the nut, but rather tighten
                    the nut a small amount to allow the keeper to be seated.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Reinstall the hub cap and gasket. Tighten the screws to 16 to 20 Lbf-ft (22 to 27 Nm).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Refill the hub cap with EP gear lube of API GL-5 quality to the fill line (0.9 pint) on
                    the hub cap.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Repeat the procedure on the opposite side.</para>
            </step1>
        </svcproc>
